Interface d_i_Queue<E>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Collection<E>, java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Queue<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    d_QueueFIFO, d_QueueLIFO, d_QueuePriority

    public interface d_i_Queue<E>
extends java.util.Queue<E>
    Artificial Intelligence A Modern Approach (3rd Edition): pg 79.

    The operations on a queue are as follows:
    • EMPTY?(queue) returns true only if there are no elements in the queue
    • POP(queue) removes teh first element of the queue and returns it.
    • INSERT(element, queue) inserts and element and returns the resulting queue.
    Note: This extends the java.util.Queue collections interface in order to take advantage of pre-existing implementations. The intent of this interface is purely to provide an interface to Queues that corresponds to what is described in AIMA3e.
    Author:
    Ravi Mohan, Ciaran O'Reilly
